The article discusses a summit on UN peacekeeping that was co-hosted by Vice President Joe Biden and UN Secretary-General Ban Ki-moon. The summit aimed to address the challenges faced by peacekeeping missions, such as increasing numbers, operating in dangerous environments, and outdated infrastructure. Several countries made commitments to strengthen UN peacekeeping, including troop deployments, contributions of enablers like aviation and engineering units, and pledges to protect civilians from violence. The United States reaffirmed its support for peacekeeping, highlighting its financial contributions and investments in capacity-building efforts. The US also contributes uniformed personnel, including police officers and military personnel, to UN peacekeeping operations.